    • setDeprecated

      public void setDeprecated(boolean deprecated)
      Sets whether or not the API element is deprecated.

      Deprecated elements are shown in the WebUI with a note that they are deprecated and their use is discouraged. The API generators might also mark the elements as deprecated.

      Parameters:
      deprecated - true if the API element is deprecated, false otherwise.
      Since:
      2.6.0
      See Also:
      • setDeprecatedDescription(String)

    • setDeprecatedDescription

      public void setDeprecatedDescription(String description)
      Sets the (concise) description of the deprecation.

      The description should explain why it was deprecated and what are the alternative endpoints that should be used, if any.

      Note: It should be in plain text (i.e. no HTML tags).

      Parameters:
      description - the description of the deprecation.
      Since:
      2.6.0
      See Also:
      • setDeprecated(boolean)
